---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import APIDocsLayout from "../../components/APIDocsLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Client Libraries — +254 API Reference">
  <APIDocsLayout activeSection="clients">
    <header class="page-heading">
      <h1>Client Libraries</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-eyebrow">Python</h2>
      <div class="narrative">
        <p>Install the Python client library to work with +254 data in pandas and Jupyter:</p>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>pip install plus254</code></pre>
      <div class="narrative">
        <p>Once installed, import and query:</p>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>from plus254 import Client

client = Client()
tea = client.dataset("tea", source="teaboard")
df = tea.to_pandas()
df.head()</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-eyebrow">JavaScript / TypeScript</h2>
      <div class="narrative">
        <p>Use the JavaScript client for Node.js and browser environments:</p>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>npm install plus254</code></pre>
      <div class="narrative">
        <p>Query datasets using async/await:</p>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>import &#123; Plus254 &#125; from "plus254";

const api = new Plus254();
const data = await api.dataset("tea", &#123; source: "teaboard" &#125;);
console.log(data);</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-eyebrow">R</h2>
      <div class="narrative">
        <p>Install the R package from CRAN:</p>
      </div>
      <pre class="code-block"><code>install.packages("plus254")
library(plus254)

tea <- get_dataset("teaboard", "tea")
head(tea)</code></pre>
    </section>

    <a href="/api-docs/errors/" class="next-btn">Next: Error Handling <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></a>
  </APIDocsLayout>
</BaseLayout>
